<div class="hero">
    <h1>🔍 Search Cities</h1>
    <p>Find cities worldwide by name, country, or coordinates</p>
</div>

<div class="search-container">
    <div class="card">
        <h2>City Search</h2>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
            <input 
                type="text" 
                id="city-search" 
                class="search-input" 
                placeholder="Enter city name (e.g., London, Tokyo, New York)"
                style="flex: 1; min-width: 300px;"
            >
            <button onclick="searchCities(document.getElementById('city-search').value)" class="btn">
                Search
            </button>
        </div>
        
        <div style="margin-top: 1rem; color: var(--dracula-comment);">
            <small>💡 Start typing to see live results. Minimum 2 characters required.</small>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="results-container">
    <div id="search-results"></div>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2>🎯 Search Tips</h2>
    <ul style="list-style: none; padding-left: 0;">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">• Type at least 2 characters to start searching</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">• Search is case-insensitive</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">• Results show city name, country code, and coordinates</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">• City IDs are compatible with OpenWeatherMap API</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">• Use country codes (e.g., "US", "GB", "JP") to filter by country</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h2>📡 API Usage</h2>
    <p>You can also use our API directly:</p>
    
    <h3>Search by name:</h3>
    <pre><code>GET /api/v1/cities/search?q=london&limit=10</code></pre>
    
    <h3>Search by country:</h3>
    <pre><code>GET /api/v1/cities/country/US?limit=50</code></pre>
    
    <h3>Get specific city:</h3>
    <pre><code>GET /api/v1/cities/2643743</code></pre>
    
    <p style="margin-top: 1rem;">
        <a href="/docs" class="btn">📚 View Full Documentation</a>
    </p>
</div>